column3: Automatic sanity-testing: PASSED, see http://jenkins.bluematt.me/pull-tester/c63791170b55a5bcffc7e631fb42ef462706eb3a for binaries and test log.\nThis test script verifies pulls every time they are updated. It, however, dies sometimes and fails to test properly.  If you are waiting on a test, please check timestamps to verify that the test.log is moving at http://jenkins.bluematt.me/pull-tester/cu
Decided that this is essentially two separate issues that should be in separate pulls. Going to close this and open separate ones in the future.\n
What is this doing here? Thought this is Mac OpenSSL related :).\n
@Diapolo bitcoin-qt.pro has changed since I originally created the patch. So as well as adding the openssl lib defines, it brings the patch up to date.\n
